data.text: @anattack001 Me either. When it's deserved and they haven't won, yes, give it to those who habe been hustling. I hate a pity Oscar, especially when someone else deserved it more that year, but alas. Oldman and Chastain are deserving, long over due, and really, top candidates this year

@Potszicle Absolutely. Again, it’s time for new deserving faces to start winning the awards. With the exception of long time favorites like Oldman and Chastain who have time and time again proven themselves. I wouldn’t be mad if either won.
@anattack001 Me too!! I hope the Oscars consider and award him haha
@anattack001 Action Ensamble. A booboo nomination, which I'm pretty sure they get every year

@anattack001 How the Oscars play out, and I'm also hopeful for different people with every new nominations list. For inztance, Laurie Metcalf for Lady Bird... She keeps getting recognized for it, so this might be her year. I get so anxious haha

@anattack001 A strong list! Practically identical to the Golden Globes, except SAG nominated TWD. I found it interesting that they considered Steve Carrel supporting, though, and skipped over Armie. It's funny how Jeffrey Tambour was deliberately skipped this year, too. I'm curious to see...
